        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 13 at 3:56PM EDT by NWS Wilmington NC</headline>
        <description>At 356 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Southeastern Community College, or near Whiteville, moving northeast
at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Whiteville, Elizabethtown, Chadbourn, Bladenboro, Boardman, Carvers,
Abbottsburg, Lisbon, Lagoon, Elkton, Council, Emerson, Southeastern
Community College, Evergreen, Kelly, Clarkton, White Lake, and Bladen
County Hospital.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
